<h1><span>Q&amp;A:</span></h1>
<h2><span>Q: Can I replace a blurb that you wrote for one of my articles with my own? I'm not satisfied with it.</span></h2>
<p>A: Absolutely. You will always have that option at any point.</p>
<h2><span>Q: I noticed an error/typo/incorrect information and wish to correct it. May I?</span></h2>
<p>A: Sure! If the changes are not limited to your own article(s) and/or are substantial changes across multiple entries, you should post in that month's discussion page and then make the changes.</p>
<h2><span>Q: I wrote an article and it seems to have stuck. Can I send a blurb of mine to one of the frequent collaborators?</span></h2>
<p>A: Yup! It's much easier if you come to us about it, and it gives you the control over what you want shown on the news page.</p>
